{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"succinct-formable-kite","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Author a ticket plan (or code diff) that references a valid THIRD-PARTY library symbol which has zero occurrences in the rebar repo — e.g. `pydantic_ai.exceptions.ContentFilterError` or `IncompleteToolCall` (both importable at pydantic-ai 1.107.0; reproduce: `python -c 'from pydantic_ai.exceptions import ContentFilterError, IncompleteToolCall'` exits 0).\n2. Run `rebar review-plan <id>` (or the code-review gate).\n3. The LLM reviewer emits BLOCK findings across multiple criteria (observed on E4/G1G2/G6/T1/T8) asserting the symbol 'does not exist anywhere in the rebar codebase or in pydantic-ai's exception surface' / 'produces zero search hits'.\n\n## Observed contrast (discriminating evidence)\n- Symbols that DO appear in the rebar repo are NOT flagged: `ModelHTTPError` and `UsageLimitExceeded` (both imported in `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`) pass, while `ContentFilterError`/`IncompleteToolCall` (equally valid, but absent from rebar src/tests) are flagged absent. The trigger is 'referenced symbol has zero occurrences in the rebar repo', not 'symbol is actually absent'.\n- No amount of prose remediation (inline reproduce-commands, 'this is a library symbol' notes) clears it; the finding recurs every re-review. This is the exact 'code-blind reviewer' false-positive the epic jira-reb-687 pre-emptively documented for the `[retries]` extra.\n\n## Root cause\nThe DET grounding ORACLE is correct: `src/rebar/grounding/oracle.py:refute_absence` routes a `symbol`/`import`/`member` reference to the T1 ctags lane and, per its contract, 'NEVER asserts an absence' — it ABSTAINS when it cannot resolve a symbol. The false-positive originates in the LLM reviewer TIER (plan-review pass-1 finder / pass-2 verifier), whose code-read file tools are scoped to the rebar repo snapshot (`pai_tools.filesystem_tools(cfg.repo_path)`, `src/rebar/llm/runner.py:218`). The reviewer cannot read the installed third-party packages in the venv's site-packages, so it reasons 'I searched the codebase, found no such symbol, therefore it does not exist' and emits a BLOCK — unbounded by the oracle's abstain discipline. Third-party library symbols are structurally invisible to the reviewer, so every plan/diff that references one risks a false BLOCK.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: a referenced symbol the reviewer cannot locate in the repo but which MAY be a third-party library symbol is treated as UNVERIFIABLE (abstain / no finding), mirroring the grounding oracle's 'never assert absence' discipline — not asserted absent.\n- Actual: the LLM reviewer asserts the symbol is nonexistent and BLOCKs, producing unremediable false-positive gate failures for any plan referencing a valid library symbol.\n\n## Impact\nBlocks legitimate plans/diffs whenever they name a third-party symbol absent from the rebar repo; forces either lossy rephrasing (removing precise, correct symbol references from plans) or `--force` claim bypass. Degrades the plan-review gate's trustworthiness (false BLOCKs) and wastes ~10-min review cycles per iteration.\n\n## Suggested fix directions (pick one, design first)\n- Route the reviewer's symbol-existence claims through the grounding oracle (which abstains), so the LLM cannot directly assert absence of a symbol.\n- Give the reviewer a bounded symbol-resolution tool over the RUNTIME environment (`importlib.util.find_spec` / import probe / ctags over installed deps), so third-party symbols resolve.\n- Prompt-instruct the finder/verifier to ABSTAIN (not refute) on a symbol it cannot locate in-repo when it could plausibly be a third-party library symbol, mirroring `oracle.refute_absence`'s 'never assert absence' contract.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A plan/diff that references a valid third-party library symbol absent from the rebar repo (e.g. `ContentFilterError`) does NOT produce a 'symbol does not exist' BLOCK finding.\n- [ ] The reviewer either resolves the symbol against the runtime environment or abstains — it never asserts absence of a symbol it merely cannot see in the repo snapshot.\n- [ ] A regression test injects a plan referencing a known-importable third-party symbol and asserts no absence-BLOCK is produced.\n- [ ] Symbols genuinely absent everywhere (repo AND runtime) still surface (no loss of true-positive absence detection).\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green.","id":"406f-7a43-fb96-47a9","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["plan-review","grounding","false-positive"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Plan/code-review LLM grounding false-positives 'symbol does not exist' on third-party library symbols (repo-scoped read tools can't see site-packages)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783629616393433001,"uuid":"c74f8a33-ee49-4ef7-8e0d-ae53dee1371a"}